{
  "text": "As an initial condition for the gradient descent, we moved the chosen template B to the location of the average deformation field from B to all other controls. This definition of a 'vector mean' template has been adopted by others [CITATION_1] , but here we optimize it using a further deformation to yield a template with minimal energy in the multivariate log-Euclidean space. Using a finite difference scheme in the computation of the gradient yields poor results, as a small number of voxels with large gradient values can end up driving the computation, and in such cases most of the image will change very slowly. We remedied this problem using a multi-resolution scheme, for which all derivatives in (5) were computed through convolution with a Gaussian filter, for which the variance was reduced at each resolution step. To improve the speed of convergence, the positions were updated after the computation of the descent direction for each i.",
  "citation_candidates": [
